<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03144d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03144d">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03144d"> 144(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Is &amp; Arthur / her ruse</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The Ordeal by Red-hot Iron]</font> &ldquo;Sir, my lady requires of you to be on the White Plain on the appointed day, in a pilgrim&apos;s gown, <mark>so skillfully disguised that none may recognise you</mark>, and unarmed. To reach the place of judgment, she will have to cross the river in a boat; you are to await her in the opposite shore, where King Arthur&apos;s knights will be gathered. Doubtless you will then be able to help her. My lady dreads the day of the ordeal; nevertheless, she trusts to the courtesy of God, who saved her from the hands of the lepers.&rdquo; <small> Joseph B&eacute;dier, <a name="JBLR1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JBLR1"><cite title="source">Le roman de Tristan et Iseut</cite></a> (1900) XII &lsquo;Le Jugement par le Fer Rouge&rsquo;, 135</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
